title: Seo Taiji - [&] (Special Edition Discography) (Korean 2007)
description:
This is [&] - the limited-edition discography compilation released by Seo Taiji in 2007.

It contains all 7 of his studio albums, the first four from his career with Seo Taiji & Boys and the other 3 from his solo career to date.  This compilation spans his career from 1991 to 2007, each disc complemented with re-mixes, live performances, and re-interpretations in addition to the original tracks.

In a country filled with cookie-cutter annoying pop-groups Seo Taiji breaks the mold... Though to Western ears, he sounds like a ripoff artist, he single-handedly introduced hip-hop then metal to Korea.  His early albums sound a lot like Cypress Hill while later albums sound like Korn...  In any case, he may well be the savior of Korean music.
